doc.previous: All ULDs are identified by their ULD number A three letter prefix identifies its type followed by a 4 or 5 digit serial number 4 if prior to October 1 1993 either 4 or 5 if after October 1 1993 to uniquely identify it from others of the same type and ending with a two character alpha numerical suffix identifying the ULD s owner if an airline often the same as IATA designator codes For example AKN 12345 DL means that the ULD is a forkliftable LD3 with the unique number 12345 and its owner is Delta Air Lines 10
